SUMMARY:ASSIMILATION AND INTEGRITY -  Art Exhibition by Tatjana Hutinec
DESCRIPTION:“ASSIMILATION AND INTEGRITY”\,  solo art exhibition by Tatjana Hutinec\, features two interconnected bodies of work: \nDrawing on her Croatian heritage and folklore within figurative and allegorical imagery\, work by Tatjana Hutinec celebrates cultural identity within Canadian multiculturalism while the unstable and stormy skyscapes and cloud paintings address contemporary questions of identity and belonging shaped by lived experience of migration\, cultural displacement and the pressures of assimilation \n \nASSIMILATION AND INTEGRITY – Art Exhibition by Tatjana Hutinec \nASSEMBLY HALL  – 1 Colonel Samuel Smith Park Dr.\, Toronto  \n \nEXHIBITION RUNS: April 2- May 7\, 2026 \nOpen: Mon – Fri  10- 5     Sat 10 -1\,             Closed: Apr 3 and Apr 6 \n \nOPENING RECEPTION: Wednesday\, April 8\,  from 5:30 – 8 PM \n \nARTIST TALK: Saturday – Apr 11 & Saturday – Apr 18\,    from 11– 1 \n \nPreview Art: www.tatjanahutinec.com
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/assimilation-and-integrity-art-exhibition-by-tatjana-hutinec/
LOCATION:Assembly Hall\, 1 Colonel Samuel Smith Park Drive\, Etobicoke\, M8V 4B6
CATEGORIES:Art & Design,Exhibitions,Talks & Panels
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/assimilation-and-integrity-art-exhibition-by-tatjana-hutinec.png
END:VEVENT
