SUMMARY:Music in the Afternoon presents Stéphane Tétreault
DESCRIPTION:Multi award-winning cellist Stéphane Tétreault presents an intriguing program that blends cello and bandoneon\, joined by bandoneonist Denis Plante and pianist Chloé Dumoulin. \nFrom Johann Sebastian Bach to Astor Piazzolla to Plante’s own works\, this diverse program explores the ear-tickling possibilities of this exotic instrumental partnership. \nArrive at 12:15 pm for a free pre-concert chat with our new Artistic Director\, Amy Hillis.
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/music-in-the-afternoon-presents-stephane-tetreault/
LOCATION:Walter Hall\, 80 Queens Park\, Toronto\, ON M5S 2C5\, Canada\, Old Toronto\, Toronto\, Ontario\, M5S 2C5
CATEGORIES:Live Music,Performing Arts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/music-in-the-afternoon-presents-stephane-tetreault.png
END:VEVENT
